			section
				h3.r-fit-text A Brief History of Audio Automation

				aside.notes.
					Before music could be recorded, to hear music, you would have to play it yourself or find somebody to play it for you. 

					You could sing or play an instrument. 

					The best music was made together by groups - collectives of individuals performing together. 

					Choirs and orchestras sounded bigger and more powerful than individuals alone.

					Played together, sounds complement each other. 

					Constructive coherance.
			
			section
				h3.r-fit-text Orkhēstra
				aside.notes.
					Orchestras were named after the word for the dedicated room in ancient Greek theatres for dancing to music.

					The quantity of new musical instruments grew to cover all the different pitch and timbre combinations. 

					Orchestras grew exponentially.

					Soon, musical instruments became as expressive as singing.

					And the complexity to play them grew to represent this broad musical range.

					Complexity bred discontent.

					And so, for as long as we have been making music with instruments, we have been trying to find ways to automate the process. 
					

			section 
				video( data-autoplay, muted, src="/static/talk/piano-roll.mp4").full-size.wallpaper.woodblock 
				aside.notes.
					There were church organs that used piano-rolls - punch cards with holes cut out in sequences to play the corresponding notes on the organ, or the church bell sequencer…

			section
