				aside.notes.
					True joy comes from the act of creation, the personal expression, the feelings of representation, ownership, and the ability to share that finished piece with your friends.


					With music, the end result is your prize for participation, something that holds a deep personal connection.

					You have invested your time and expression, and converted it into something that perfectly encapsulates. 


					TODO:
					Music is kind of like an infinitely rewarding video game with unlimited levels, no high score and a satisfying prize for everybody at the end.
			

					TODO: 
										
					Instruments are designed to play together so their sonic outputs need to harmonize and sound complementary to one another. 

					The cello improves the sound of the violin, which expands on the sound of the viola for example. 

					These instruments speak the same language.
					In fact all instruments speak a similar language.

			section
				blockquote 
					p.r-fit-text You’re limited by your language, by your vocabulary. You think with your language, so your language dictates how you think. But when you’re making music, it doesn’t. That’s why I love making music so much.
					cite Richard D James

				aside.notes.
					Music is just patterns of air.

					Whether ingrained or part of a learned musical lexicon- the rules for music are firmly established and can be quantified, defined and synthesised.

					A happy song can be written with major chords which sound elevating and uplifting, whereas a sad song can be written using a minor scale that gives it an air of melancholy and malaise.

					Choirs around the world harmonise together without worrying about tuning or scales.

					Instruments were created to replicate these tones and thus a common musical language naturally emerged.

					It appears that periodicity is a characteristic of all phenomena of nature.


			section
				blockquote 
					p.r-fit-text Music is an unconscious exercise in metaphysics in which the mind is unaware that it is philosophizing.

					cite Arthur Schopenhauer

				aside.notes.
					Whether or not this language is entirely intrinsic is debated, but certainly elements are universal, such as the common sounds of mumese, the language we employ to speak to babies or cute animals.

					We automatically raise our pitch and speak softly when communicating with babies and small animals. as we expect that is how they sound. 

					In the same way that birds didn’t go to school to learn how to sing, mumese appears to be a birthright, an intrinsic universal communication system - all built in, ready to go. 

					An instinct.

			section
				figure
					img(src="/static/talk/tb303.png")
					figcaption
						small Roland TB303 Bassline Generator

				aside.notes.
					The Roland TB303 synthesizer contains an electronic filter that unintentionally mimics the distress cries of animals, where the instrument wails, shrieks and squeals - speaking to us on a primordial level, guided subconsciously by thousands of years of evolution in the wilderness, where we relied upon sound, which communicated with us before language.

					This is the power of music - an innate language at the physiological level - you don’t just hear it, you feel it, you react to it. 

			section
				blockquote 
					p.r-fit-text Music is an unconscious exercise in mathematics in which the mind is unaware that it is calculating
					cite Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz

				aside.notes.
					Music affects us in profound ways.

					Before these modern times, it was not uncommon for a belief in the concept of the sound ether, one of the four stages in the creation of matter, where sound is crucial as the force that gives a substance its preliminary shape and form. 

					Which sounds relatively similar to the Bose-Einstein condensate...
					I mean
					They didn’t call it the big bang because they thought it was silent!

					A Quantum physicist was not impressed by that analogy, explaining to me how without air, there could be no sound, whilst completely disregarding the fact that there could be no ears there to hear it.

			section
				blockquote 
