			section
				h3 Practise, Practise!
				aside.notes.
					Most musical instruments don’t come easily.

					So rather than requiring someone to alter their physical expression to work with an instrument, how about we alter the instrument to work with that person’s expressions?

					A musical instrument that plays you?

					What if we could make an instrument that converts your intrinsic intentions into auditory expressions?

					Your moods into music?

					It becomes so much easier to learn a  physical skill when it is based on your natural movements, so that you can express yourself in the way that you feel most comfortable.

					Repetition encourages humans to learn patterns.

					Repetition is reassuring.
		
			section
				blockquote 
					p.r-fit-text Repetition serves as the handprint for human intent
					cite Elizabeth Hellmuth Margulis

				aside.notes.
					What would a musical instrument look like that uses your motions and emotions as the basis for an auditory ones?

			section

				aside.notes.
					Well, we could use automation to provide the foundational structure and Machine learning to extract our intentions, reflecting our expression through  appropriate sounds. 

					Sound directly inspired by you, where the music follows the dance.
										
					Rather than using machines and automation to replace the act of creation - the playing of the game - we can instead use it to replace the process.


