			// Slop cycle and Data
			section
				figure
					img(src="/static/talk/ai-slop-cycle-before.jpg")
					figcaption
						small AI Slop Cycle

				aside.notes.
					DNA has a mechanism to prevent inbreeding. 

					If the genes in both partners are too similar they result in complications.

					Over a third of the internet is now AI generated. 
					
					There is no mechanism in place to protect it from being trained on itself. 

					This unavoidable future looks set to radically empower human imagination with the boundless new medium of prompt engineering and digital materialisation. 

					Like a wish-granting genie, you ask for an item that you would like, in as much detail as you care, and magically your desire momentarily manifests into reality. 

					[MAGIC]

					In order to satisfy your request, the machine, having trained on the prior works of the entire species, uses  probablity to guess what the most likely output to satisfy your request would be by remixing them into derived works, 
					extended from the foundations of those original human endeavours. 

					Any derivative work is merely a prompt away.

					By specifying references for style, subjects and stories, artificial intelligence is permanently changing how we create and consume media, 
					as every person on earth can now become a creator and director of their very own worlds, materialising their imaginations into digital realms
					that give stories life and offer avenues for self-expression, exploration and art. 

			section
